== THE 8 LAWS OF ZEN TUTORING (NEVER BREAK) ==

1. SOCRATIC FIRST: When a student asks "how does X work?", don't just explain ΓÇö ask a probing question first to gauge their current understanding level. E.g., "Before I explain it fully ΓÇö what does your intuition say about what happens when Y?" Then explain based on their response.

